 0.003564      0.909851      0.998430  SEKER  \n","2     0.908774      0.007244      0.003048      0.825871      0.999066  SEKER  \n","3     0.928329      0.007017      0.003215      0.861794      0.994199  SEKER  \n","4     0.970516      0.006697      0.003665      0.941900      0.999166  SEKER  \n","\n","Feature matrix shape: (13611, 16)\n","Labels shape: (13611,)\n"]}],"source":["file_path = '/kaggle/input/dry-bean-dataset/Dry_Bean_Dataset/Dry_Bean_Dataset.xlsx'\n","sh_name = 'Dry_Beans_Dataset'\n","df = pd.read_excel(file_path, sheet_name=sh_name)\n","\n","print(\"Dataset shape:\", df.shape)\n","print(\"Columns:\", df.columns.tolist())\n","print(\"\\nFirst few rows:\")\n","print(df.head())\n","\n","features = df.iloc[:, :16].values  \n","bean_type = df.iloc[:, 16].values\n","\n","print(f\"\\nFeature matrix shape: {features.shape}\")\n","print(f\"Labels shape: {bean_type.shape}\")"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"22aa2861","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.003944,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.156492","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.152548","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### 3.2. Standardization\n","\n","Before getting into the actual PCA algorithm, since the data has different scales for different labels, we will standardize the data."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":3,"id":"c0bfb616","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.166348Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.165934Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.196447Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.195324Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.038192,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.198596","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.160404","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["\n","Data standardized. Shape: (13611, 16)\n"]}],"source":["n_components = 2\n","\n","mean = np.mean(features, axis=0)\n","sig = np.std(features, axis=0)\n","x_centre = features-mean\n","x_stand = x_centre / sig\n","\n","print(f\"\\nData standardized. Shape: {x_stand.shape}\")\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"6ab47573","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.004556,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.208929","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.204373","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### 3.3. Covariance and Eigenvalue\n","\n","We will compute the covariance matrix of the standardized data, which will describe how each feature varies with other features and since PCA needs eigendecomposition, we will compute the eigenvectors and the eigenvalues"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":4,"id":"77917892","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.219069Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.218603Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.253899Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.252626Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.042759,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.255638","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.212879","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["Covariance matrix shape: (16, 16)\n","Eigenvalues shape: (16,)\n","Eigenvectors shape: (16, 16)\n"]}],"source":["\n","n_samples = features.shape[0]\n","cov_matrix = np.dot(x_stand.T, x_stand) / (n_samples - 1)\n","\n","print(f\"Covariance matrix shape: {cov_matrix.shape}\")\n","\n","e_val, e_vec = np.linalg.eig(cov_matrix)\n","\n","print(f\"Eigenvalues shape: {e_val.shape}\")\n","print(f\"Eigenvectors shape: {e_vec.shape}\")\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"31cf93c9","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.005019,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.264913","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.259894","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### 3.4. Eigenvalues and Eigenvector sorting\n","We will then sort eigenvectors by their eigenvalues in descending order and select the top components, which is in this case, 2.\n","\n","After that, we project the standardized data. Also, we will show the reduced data shape and the Information Retention Ratio, and the total variance retained."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":5,"id":"8eebc17c","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.275511Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.274719Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.285977Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.285108Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.018526,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.287497","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.268971","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["\n","Selected 2 principal components\n","Components shape: (16, 2)\n","Reduced data shape: (13611, 2)\n","\\Information Retention ratio: [0.55466439 0.26430973]\n","Total variance retained: 81.90%\n"]}],"source":["idx = np.argsort(e_val)[::-1]\n","e_val_sorted = e_val[idx]\n","e_vec_sorted = e_vec[:, idx]\n","\n","components = e_vec_sorted[:, :n_components]\n","selected_eigenvalues = e_val_sorted[:n_components]\n","\n","print(f\"\\nSelected {n_components} principal components\")\n","print(f\"Components shape: {components.shape}\")\n","\n","reduced_feat = np.dot(x_stand, components)\n","\n","print(f\"Reduced data shape: {reduced_feat.shape}\")\n","\n","info_ratio = selected_eigenvalues / np.sum(e_val)\n","print(f\"\\Information Retention ratio: {info_ratio}\")\n","print(f\"Total variance retained: {np.sum(info_ratio):.2%}\")\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"4b7ca810","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.0057,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.298493","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.292793","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### 3.5. Plotting\n","\n","We will plot the 2D data created after reducing the dimensionality, and show the scatter plot for bean types. (Different types shown by different colors.). Also, we will"]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":6,"id":"c9d14429","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.308568Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.30826Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.521088Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.52001Z"},"papermill":{"duration":1.220897,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.52361","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:18.302713","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"image/png":"\n","text/plain":["<Figure size 1200x800 with 2 Axes>"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"},{"data":{"image/png":"\n","text/plain":["<Figure size 1500x500 with 2 Axes>"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"},{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["\n","Number of components needed for 95% variance: 4\n"]}],"source":["plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))\n","\n","scatter = plt.scatter(reduced_feat[:, 0], reduced_feat[:, 1], \n","                     c=pd.factorize(bean_type)[0], \n","                     cmap='viridis', \n","                     alpha=0.6,\n","                     s=20)\n","\n","plt.xlabel(f'PC1 ({info_ratio[0]:.2%} variance)')\n","plt.ylabel(f'PC2 ({info_ratio[1]:.2%} variance)')\n","plt.title('PCA of Bean Dataset - 2D Projection')\n","plt.colorbar(scatter, label='Bean Type')\n","plt.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n","\n","\n","all_var_ratio = e_val_sorted / np.sum(e_val)\n","cum_var = np.cumsum(all_var_ratio)\n","\n","fig, (ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(15, 5))\n","\n","\n","ax1.bar(range(1, len(all_var_ratio) + 1), all_var_ratio)\n","ax1.set_xlabel('Principal Component')\n","ax1.set_ylabel('Information Retention Ratio')\n","ax1.set_title('Information Retention by Each Component')\n","ax1.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n","\n","ax2.plot(range(1, len(cum_var) + 1), cum_var, 'bo-')\n","ax2.axhline(y=0.95, color='r', linestyle='--', label='95% variance')\n","ax2.set_xlabel('Number of Components')\n","ax2.set_ylabel('Cumulative Variance Explained')\n","ax2.set_title('Cumulative Variance Explained')\n","ax2.legend()\n","ax2.grid(True, alpha=0.3)\n","\n","plt.tight_layout()\n","plt.show()\n","\n","print(f\"\\nNumber of components needed for 95% variance: {np.argmax(cum_var >= 0.95) + 1}\")\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"a73d1c39","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.012429,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.549263","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.536834","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["## 4. KNN Classifier\n","\n","### 4.1. Data Split\n","\n","As usual with other common practices, we will seed the random as 42, and split the training and testing data into 80/20."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":7,"id":"ea64a77c","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.575336Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.574637Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.583751Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.58239Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.023763,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.585273","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.56151","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["\n","Training set size: 10888\n","Testing set size: 2723\n"]}],"source":["np.random.seed(42)\n","n_sample_total = reduced_feat.shape[0]\n","indices = np.random.permutation(n_sample_total)\n","split_idx = int(0.8 * n_sample_total)\n","\n","train_indices = indices[:split_idx]\n","test_indices = indices[split_idx:]\n","\n","x_train = reduced_feat[train_indices]\n","y_train = bean_type[train_indices]\n","x_test = reduced_feat[test_indices]\n","y_test = bean_type[test_indices]\n","\n","print(f\"\\nTraining set size: {x_train.shape[0]}\")\n","print(f\"Testing set size: {x_test.shape[0]}\")\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"e6b72496","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.012085,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.609364","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.597279","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### 4.2. KNN Implementation\n","\n","We will define the euclidean distance since we will be using this equation a lot.\n","After that, we will iterate through the sample, compute the distance to every training sample, sort them by the distance, select the 'K Nearest Neighbors' and choose the predicted label."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":8,"id":"84a99e4e","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.635588Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.635191Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.643224Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.642062Z"},"papermill":{"duration":0.023351,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.644948","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.621597","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[],"source":["\n","def euclidean_distance(point1, point2):\n","    return np.sqrt(np.sum((point1 - point2) ** 2))\n","\n","def knn_predict(X_train, y_train, x_test, k):\n","    \n","    distances = []\n","    for i in range(len(X_train)):\n","        dist = euclidean_distance(x_test, X_train[i])\n","        distances.append((dist, y_train[i]))\n","    \n","    distances.sort(key=lambda x: x[0])\n","    k_nearest = distances[:k]\n","    k_nearest_labels = [label for (_, label) in k_nearest]\n","    \n","    unique_labels, counts = np.unique(k_nearest_labels, return_counts=True)\n","    return unique_labels[np.argmax(counts)]\n","\n","def knn_predict_all(X_train, y_train, X_test, k):\n","    predictions = []\n","    for i in range(len(X_test)):\n","        pred = knn_predict(X_train, y_train, X_test[i], k)\n","        predictions.append(pred)\n","    return np.array(predictions)\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"9be28312","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.011832,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.66866","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.656828","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### 4.3. Train & Testing KNN\n","\n","We will use the previously split training set and the test set here. The training set will be used to find nearest neighbors,and the test set will be used to evaluate performance. \n","\n","We will test KNN for several values of k, since we do not know the optimal k value that will give us the most accurate data that is not overfitted.\n","\n","After that, we will calculate the accuracy and record the most accurate(best) k for future use. However, since we reduced the dimensionality quite a lot, we will not get a 95% accuracy."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":9,"id":"43de86d3","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.694467Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.694023Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-20T01:34:58.886771Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-20T01:34:58.885324Z"},"papermill":{"duration":1479.218208,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:34:58.899094","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:10:19.680886","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["\n","Testing KNN with different k values...\n","------------------------------------------------------------\n","\n","Testing with k=3...\n","Accuracy: 0.8454 (84.54%)\n","\n","Testing with k=5...\n","Accuracy: 0.8549 (85.49%)\n","\n","Testing with k=7...\n","Accuracy: 0.8656 (86.56%)\n","\n","Testing with k=9...\n","Accuracy: 0.8667 (86.67%)\n","\n","Testing with k=11...\n","Accuracy: 0.8689 (86.89%)\n","\n","Testing with k=13...\n","Accuracy: 0.8700 (87.00%)\n","\n","Testing with k=15...\n","Accuracy: 0.8704 (87.04%)\n","\n","============================================================\n","BEST RESULT: k=15 with accuracy=0.8704 (87.04%)\n","============================================================\n"]}],"source":["\n","k_values = [3, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 15]\n","\n","print(\"\\nTesting KNN with different k values...\")\n","print(\"-\" * 60)\n","\n","best_k = None\n","best_accuracy = 0\n","\n","for k in k_values:\n","    print(f\"\\nTesting with k={k}...\")\n","    y_pred = knn_predict_all(x_train, y_train, x_test, k)\n","    \n","    accuracy = np.sum(y_pred == y_test) / len(y_test)\n","    \n","    print(f\"Accuracy: {accuracy:.4f} ({accuracy*100:.2f}%)\")\n","    \n","    if accuracy > best_accuracy:\n","        best_accuracy = accuracy\n","        best_k = k\n","\n","print(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*60)\n","print(f\"BEST RESULT: k={best_k} with accuracy={best_accuracy:.4f} ({best_accuracy*100:.2f}%)\")\n","print(\"=\"*60)\n"]},{"cell_type":"markdown","id":"da0bf017","metadata":{"papermill":{"duration":0.011907,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:34:58.924049","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:34:58.912142","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"source":["### 4.4. Visualization\n","\n","We will use a confusion matrix with true labels as rows, and predictions as columns. Each cell in the matrix will show the number of samples classified, thus showing us the performance on a class basis.\n","\n","After that, we will also compute the class accuracy for all 7 classes, the number of wrong predictions, and some samples of wrong predictions to show if there are any, patterns in the wrong predictions.\n","\n","And to visualize that further, we will use scatterplots to compare class boundaries."]},{"cell_type":"code","execution_count":10,"id":"b6c6923a","metadata":{"execution":{"iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-20T01:34:58.951492Z","iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-20T01:34:58.950233Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-20T01:38:29.56491Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-20T01:38:29.563874Z"},"papermill":{"duration":210.637101,"end_time":"2026-03-20T01:38:29.573179","exception":false,"start_time":"2026-03-20T01:34:58.936078","status":"completed"},"tags":[]},"outputs":[{"data":{"image/png":"\n","text/plain":["<Figure size 1000x800 with 2 Axes>"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"},{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["\n","Per-class accuracy:\n","----------------------------------------\n","BARBUNYA       : 0.5354 (53.54%)\n","BOMBAY         : 1.0000 (100.00%)\n","CALI           : 0.8248 (82.48%)\n","DERMASON       : 0.9139 (91.39%)\n","HOROZ          : 0.9655 (96.55%)\n","SEKER          : 0.9369 (93.69%)\n","SIRA           : 0.8480 (84.80%)\n"]},{"data":{"image/png":"\n","text/plain":["<Figure size 1600x600 with 2 Axes>"]},"metadata":{},"output_type":"display_data"},{"name":"stdout","output_type":"stream","text":["\n","Total misclassified: 353 out of 2723 (12.96%)\n","\n","First 10 misclassifications:\n","------------------------------------------------------------\n","True: HOROZ           | Predicted: DERMASON       \n","True: DERMASON        | Predicted: SIRA           \n","True: SIRA            | Predicted: DERMASON       \n","True: BARBUNYA        | Predicted: CALI           \n","True: CALI            | Predicted: BARBUNYA       \n","True: DERMASON        | Predicted: SIRA           \n","True: SIRA            | Predicted: DERMASON       \n","True: BARBUNYA        | Predicted: CALI           \n","True: CALI            | Predicted: BARBUNYA       \n","True: CALI            | Predicted: BARBUNYA       \n"]}],"source":["\n","y_pred_final = knn_predict_all(x_train, y_train, x_test, best_k)\n","\n","\n","unique_classes = np.unique(bean_type)\n","n_classes = len(unique_classes)\n","confusion_matrix = np.zeros((n_classes, n_classes), dtype=int)\n","\n","class_to_idx = {cls: idx for idx, cls in enumerate(unique_classes)}\n","\n","for true_label, pred_label in zip(y_test, y_pred_final):\n","    true_idx = class_to_idx[true_label]\n","    pred_idx = class_to_idx[pred_label]\n","    confusion_matrix[true_idx, pred_idx] += 1\n","\n","\n","fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 8))\n","im = ax.imshow(confusion_matrix, cmap='Blues')\n","\n","cbar = plt.colorbar(im, ax=ax)\n","cbar.set_label('Number of Predictions', rotation=270, labelpad=20)\n","\n","ax.set_xticks(np.arange(n_classes))\n","ax.set_yticks(np.arange(n_classes))\n","ax.set_xticklabels(unique_classes)\n","ax.set_yticklabels(unique_classes)\n","\n","plt.setp(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha=\"right\", rotation_mode=\"anchor\")\n","\n","for i in range(n_classes):\n","    for 